Package: harf
Title: High-dimensional Adversarial Random Forests
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(person(given = c("Cesaire", "J."),
                      family = c("K.", "Fouodo"),
                      role = c("aut", "cre"),
                      email = "fouodo@leibniz-bips.de"))
Description: High-dimensional Adversarial Random Forests (HARFs) extend classical Adversarial Random Forests (ARFs) to high-dimensional settings. The method partitions the feature space into regions where joint independence within tree leaves can be more effectively achieved. Region-specific ARF models are then trained to capture local data structure and generate synthetic observations.
